==English==
===Noun===
(''grammatical terminology''): [[case]] used to indicate [[place]], or the place where, or wherein. It corresponds roughly to the English [[preposition]]s "in", "on", "at", and "by". Languages that use the locative case include [[Belarusian]], [[Czech]], [[Dyirbal]], [[Latvian]], [[Lithuanian]], [[Polish]], [[Quechua]], [[Sanskrit]], [[Serbian]], and [[Swahili]].

